<br>
When it comes to loot, the Ghoul Assassin was the one I was really crazy about. I tried to get the mask as leftovers and was even granted it once, but IVU broke and a zol knight instantly transformed me to ketchup. I leveled like hell, played as much as I coudl in XP grind groups just to reach 30 so I could join the assassin camp. Moved there and joined the camp as soon as I dinged 30. <br>
<br>
However, everyone in that group wanted the Guise of the Deciever, and I was last in queue. I stayed for over six hours, but it never got my turn. Rejoined the camp the next day. Like the time before, everyone wanted the guise, but this time it was pure random lotto on everything. The mask dropped like two minutes after I joined the group, and I won it! Five minutes later, the Supplier dropped teh Thick Banded Belt (best belt in the game back then, at least if you had a haste cloak), and I won the lotto again. Didn't bitch about it when the groupleader changed the rules retroactively so his guildmate would get it instead. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
One week later, the guise was removed from drop, and replaced with mask of deception. Many in that group never got their guises. Both items have the effect Illusion: DarkElf, but the old guise can be used by everyone, while the newer Mask Of Deception only can be used by bards and rogues. <p>Love, Edeina<br>
